    "comment": "Rationale: 7/11/2017 Pim\nFig.4: SPAR Recruits PSD-95 to F-Actin in COS cells\nFig.5: SPAR is co-localized with PSD-95 in dendritic spines, and SPAR-enlarged spines showed more intense staining for PSD-95 (Figure 5E2, arrow) compared to spines of untransfected cells (Figure 5E2, arrowhead).\n\nTogether this means that SPAR regulates recruitment of the postsynaptic scaffold.. Experimental description: Cultured hippocampal neurons were used to study the function of SIPA1L1/SPAR in regulating dendritic spine morphology.\n\nLiteral from M&M:\n\"Neuronal Culture, Transfection, and Immunostaining\nFor spine morphology studies, hippocampal primary neuronal cultures prepared from embryonic day (E) 18-19 rat embryos were plated at high density (~750 cells mm-2) (Sala et al., 2000).\"\n\n7/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed protein is of rat species: \"Complete SPAR cDNA was obtained by PCR from a rat brain Marathon library using specific primers (GenBank accession #AF026504).\"",
